<exercise checkit-seed="0000" checkit-slug="TI4" checkit-title="Trigonometric Substitution">
    <statement>
        <p>
Find the appropriate trignometric substitution for <m>x</m> and rewrite <me>\int -\frac{1}{x^{2} - 1} dx</me> as an integral in terms of <m>\theta</m>.
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        We substitute <m>x=\sin\left(\theta\right).</m>  Then <m>dx=\cos\left(\theta\right)d\theta</m> and:
        <me>
\int -\frac{1}{x^{2} - 1} dx = \int -\frac{\cos\left(\theta\right)}{\sin\left(\theta\right)^{2} - 1} d\theta = \int \frac{1}{\cos\left(\theta\right)} d\theta.
        </me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
